','2018-06-08 10:46:12'),(10068,'Holger Levsen',' In counterpoint, I\'ll add to that 4169 packages register 5318 sets of documents in doc-base. To me, that says that we\'ve got a lot of packages who are advertising their documentation this way. At the user-support BoF at the last DebConf, we also discussed how we could leverage doc-base files better','2018-10-12 06:24:35'),(10071,'Andreas Tille',' Hi all, 2018-04-25 12:21 GMT+02:00 Fabien Pichon <fabien.pichon@omictools.com>: So, using the script from Andreas, I generated a list for March and April (only 1 package for April, it can probably be merged with March). The list is available here [1]. From the 22 new packages, I excluded 4 of them ','2018-05-02 17:01:11'),(10073,'Salvatore Bonaccorso',' Hi! During triage, I realized I am sometimes a little hesitant in marking a package as no-dsa even though it\'s fairly obviously how it should be triaged. Take those two CVEs for example: https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2018-2767 mysql-5.5: fix should come with the bulk of fixes in t','2018-04-11 09:57:33'),(10075,'\"Adam D. Barratt\"',' Package: release.debian.org Severity: normal Tags: stretch User: release.debian.org@packages.debian.org Usertags: pu Dear release team, Twitter changed the character limit of tweets to 280 chars (see [1]). The version of corebird in stretch does only allow to compose tweets with 140 chars. The fix ','2017-11-20 06:41:06'),(10076,'Laurent Baillet',' Package: wnpp Severity: wishlist Owner: Laurent Baillet <laurent.baillet@gmail.com> * Package name : libai-decisiontree Version : 0.11 Upstream Author : Ken Williams <kwilliams@cpan.org> * URL : https://github.com/kenahoo/perl-ai-decisiontree * License : GPL-1+ or Artistic Programming Lang: Perl De','2018-05-11 06:55:03'),(10077,'Emilio Pozuelo Monfort',' Package: release.debian.org Severity: normal User: release.debian.org@packages.debian.org Usertags: transition Not really a transition, but binNMUs for two packages should be don