ave fun with symlinks (see the /bin/sh saga) if you wanted to be able to switch back and','2018-07-20 09:39:47'),(10240,'Paul Gevers',' On 12/23/2017 5:32 AM, john doe wrote: I tried all of this in a terminal and got :0.0 for the DISPLAY value. So I exported DISPLAY=:0.0 then ran xclip and xclip errored out because it couldn\'t find DISPLAY :0.0. \"* Connects to the X display in $DISPLAY, or specified with -display host:0\" What happe','2017-12-23 01:58:13'),(10241,'Jakub Wilk',' Jakub Wilk wrote... Thanks for proof-reading. Both issues you\'ve reported are upstream, of course I\'ll bring them there. Not sure here. Seems in English \"joker\" is unusual to describe a wildcard, unlike other languages. If some native English speaker could comment? Nice idea indeed ... Christoph si','2018-11-03 10:55:15'),(10247,'Andreas Tille',' Hi, I\'ve commited packaging for freebayes 1.1.0 to Git (Git repository became a mess which is caused by the fact that I had some local packages during freeze since new Build-Depends where needed and I failed to keep repositories in sync). The htslib issue remains the same but I have no idea how to ','2017-09-02 09:24:05'),(10248,'Wolfgang Schweer',' On Sat, Nov 04, 2017 at 10:35:16AM +0100, Dominik George wrote: Maybe just build the PulseAudio modules locally? (Versions apply to Debian Edu Stretch combi server; adjust if needed.) Login as first user (example: jdoe). sudo service xrdp stop (Make sure /etc/apt/sources.list contains a line like d','2017-11-12 12:45:46'),(10249,'Sean Whitton',' Package: debian-policy Version: 4.2.1.4 Tags: patch On Tue 30 Oct 2018 at 09:34PM -0400, Scott Kitterman wrote: I suspect we have wider project consensus for this minimal change, even if others would prefer to relax the requirement further, so I\'m optimistically going ahead and seeking seconds for ','2018-11-01 01:54:39'),(10251,'Michael Shuler',' Hi, the openssl package provides the c_rehash script which creates the links from XXXXXXXX.Y to the actual cer